A CSS rule consists of a selector and a declaration block:


selector {
  property: value;
}


Selector: Specifies the HTML element(s) to be styled.
Property: Indicates the aspect of the element to style (e.g., color, font-size).
Value: Defines the setting for the property.

p {
  color: blue;
  font-size: 16px;
}


This rule styles all <p> elements with blue text and a font size of 16 pixels.

Including CSS in HTML



